---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
    title="Breath of Life Ministries | Suicide Prevention & Mental Health Support"
    description="Breath of Life Ministries - Catholic suicide prevention ministry providing hope, support, and resources for those experiencing mental health challenges."
>
    <!-- Hero Section -->
    <section class="hero">
        <div class="hero-overlay"></div>
        <div class="container hero-content">
            <h2>You Are Not Alone</h2>
            <p>Finding hope and healing through faith, community, and compassionate support</p>
            <div class="hero-buttons">
                <a href="#get-help" class="btn btn-primary">Get Help Now</a>
                <a href="/resources" class="btn btn-secondary">Explore Resources</a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Mission Section -->
    <section class="mission">
        <div class="container">
            <h2>Our Mission</h2>
            <p class="lead">Breath of Life Ministries provides vital spiritual accompaniment for people experiencing mental health challenges and mental illness, as well as those who care for them. Rooted in Catholic teaching and compassion, we offer hope, resources, and community support for suicide prevention and mental wellness.</p>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Get Help Section -->
    <section id="get-help" class="get-help">
        <div class="container">
            <h2>Immediate Help & Support</h2>
            <div class="help-grid">
                <div class="help-card urgent">
                    <div class="help-icon">üÜò</div>
                    <h3>In Crisis?</h3>
                    <p>If you're experiencing a mental health crisis:</p>
                    <div class="crisis-contact">
                        <p><strong>Call or Text: 988</strong></p>
                        <p>National Suicide and Crisis Lifeline</p>
                        <p class="small">Available 24/7, free and confidential</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="help-card">
                    <div class="help-icon">üí¨</div>
                    <h3>Crisis Text Line</h3>
                    <p>Text <strong>HELLO</strong> to <strong>741741</strong></p>
                    <p class="small">Connect with a crisis counselor via text</p>
                </div>

                <div class="help-card">
                    <div class="help-icon">üåê</div>
                    <h3>Online Chat</h3>
                    <p>Visit <a href="https://988lifeline.org/chat/" target="_blank">988lifeline.org/chat</a></p>
                    <p class="small">Chat with a trained counselor online</p>
                </div>

                <div class="help-card">
                    <div class="help-icon">‚õ™</div>
                    <h3>Spiritual Support</h3>
                    <p>Speak with a priest or pastoral minister</p>
                    <p class="small">Find comfort in faith and community</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Catholic Teaching Section -->
    <section class="teaching">
        <div class="container">
            <h2>Catholic Teaching on Suicide & Mental Health</h2>
            <div class="teaching-content">
                <div class="teaching-text">
                    <p>The Catholic Church recognizes that suicide is a grave matter, but emphasizes God's infinite mercy and understanding of mental health issues. The Church teaches that psychological disturbances, anguish, grave fear of hardship, suffering, or torture can diminish the responsibility of the person who dies by suicide.</p>

                    <blockquote>
                        "We should not despair of the eternal salvation of persons who have taken their own lives. By ways known to him alone, God can provide the opportunity for salutary repentance."
                        <cite>- Catechism of the Catholic Church, 2283</cite>
                    </blockquote>

                    <p>Our ministry approaches mental health and suicide prevention with compassion, recognizing that those who struggle deserve our prayers, support, and accompaniment on their journey toward healing.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Programs Section -->
    <section class="programs">
        <div class="container">
            <h2>Our Programs & Services</h2>
            <div class="programs-grid">
                <div class="program-card">
                    <h3>QPR Training</h3>
                    <p><strong>Question. Persuade. Refer.</strong></p>
                    <p>Learn the 3 simple steps anyone can use to help save a life from suicide. Our training programs equip community members to recognize warning signs and intervene effectively.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="program-card">
                    <h3>Support Groups</h3>
                    <p>Connect with others who understand the challenges of mental illness or the loss of a loved one to suicide. Find community, hope, and healing in a faith-filled environment.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="program-card">
                    <h3>Grief Ministry</h3>
                    <p>Compassionate support for those who have lost a loved one to suicide. We offer specialized resources and accompaniment through the journey of grief and healing.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="program-card">
                    <h3>Education & Awareness</h3>
                    <p>Workshops, seminars, and resources to break the stigma around mental illness and promote understanding within the Catholic community.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Resources Preview -->
    <section class="resources-preview">
        <div class="container">
            <h2>Featured Resources</h2>
            <div class="resources-grid">
                <div class="resource-card">
                    <h3>When a Loved One Dies by Suicide</h3>
                    <p>Personal stories of loss, coping with grief, and finding hope through faith and community. Written by Catholics who have experienced this profound loss.</p>
                    <a href="/resources#grief" class="btn-link">Learn More ‚Üí</a>
                </div>

                <div class="resource-card">
                    <h3>Responding to Suicide</h3>
                    <p>The first book written for Catholic leaders that takes a holistic approach to understanding suicide and ministering effectively in its aftermath.</p>
                    <a href="/resources#leadership" class="btn-link">Learn More ‚Üí</a>
                </div>

                <div class="resource-card">
                    <h3>Prayer & Liturgy Resources</h3>
                    <p>Sacred resources for worship, prayer services, and liturgical guidance for mental health awareness and suicide prevention.</p>
                    <a href="/resources#prayer" class="btn-link">Learn More ‚Üí</a>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="text-center" style="margin-top: 2rem;">
                <a href="/resources" class="btn btn-primary">View All Resources</a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Contact Section -->
    <section id="contact" class="contact">
        <div class="container">
            <h2>Connect With Us</h2>
            <div class="contact-content">
                <div class="contact-info">
                    <h3>Breath of Life Ministries</h3>
                    <p>We're here to support you on your journey toward healing and hope.</p>

                    <div class="contact-details">
                        <p><strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:info@bolmsuicideprevention.com">info@bolmsuicideprevention.com</a></p>
                        <p><strong>For Ministry Support:</strong> <a href="mailto:support@bolmsuicideprevention.com">support@bolmsuicideprevention.com</a></p>
                    </div>

                    <div class="social-links">
                        <h4>Follow Us</h4>
                        <p>Stay connected for updates, resources, and hope.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="contact-form">
                    <h3>Send Us a Message</h3>
                    <form id="contactForm">
                        <div class="form-group">
                            <label for="name">Name</label>
                            <input type="text" id="name" name="name" required>
                        </div>

                        <div class="form-group">
                            <label for="email">Email</label>
                            <input type="email" id="email" name="email" required>
                        </div>

                        <div class="form-group">
                            <label for="subject">Subject</label>
                            <input type="text" id="subject" name="subject" required>
                        </div>

                        <div class="form-group">
                            <label for="message">Message</label>
                            <textarea id="message" name="message" rows="5" required></textarea>
                        </div>

                        <button type="submit" class="btn btn-primary">Send Message</button>
                    </form>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
</BaseLayout>
